        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 1:59PM EDT until June 28 at 2:15PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from 7
miles east of Ligonier to 11 miles east of Seven Springs, or along a
line from 15 miles east of Latrobe to 24 miles southeast of Latrobe,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Ligonier, Laurel Mountain and Laurel Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
